description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Emergency Nurse Practitioner (ENP) to join our small team in Withybush. We are currently alongside the Emergency Department autonomously managing patient flow in minors together with a HCSW.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be experienced and have the knowledge and skills for safe effective practice when working without direct supervision. ENPs work autonomously, determining clinical diagnosis and treatment within the current ENP scope of practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They also provide expert clinical guidance in minor injuries. The sucessful candidate must be confident and experienced in all aspects of the current scope of practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent interpersonal skills and an ability to work creatively both independently and as part of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Tuesday 17th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
